\begin_layout Part*
Von Mises distribution
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Intuitively, the Von Mises distribution
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "wolfram_von_mises"

\end_inset

 is a simple approximation for the normal distribution on a circle (known
 as the 
\shape italic
wrapped normal distribution
\shape default
).
 The Von Mises probability density function is defined by the following
 equation:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
P(x)=\frac{{e^{b\cos(x-a)}}}{2\pi I_{0}(b)}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $I_{0}(x)$
\end_inset

 is the modified Bessel function of the first kind; the Von Mises cumulative
 density function has no closed form.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The mean 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu=a$
\end_inset

 (intuitively, the angle that the distribution clustered around), and the
 circular variance 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma^{2}=1-\frac{{I_{1}(b)}}{I_{0}(b)}$
\end_inset

 (intuitively, 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset

 is the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

concentration
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 parameter).
 Therefore, as 
\begin_inset Formula $b\rightarrow0$
\end_inset

, the distribution becomes uniform; as 
\begin_inset Formula $b\rightarrow\infty$
\end_inset

, the distribution becomes normal with 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma^{2}=1/b$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section*
Von Mises-Fisher distribution
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
THe Von-Mises Fisher distribution is the generalization of the Von Mises
 distribution to 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

-dimensional hyperspheres.
 It reduces to the Von-Mises distribution with 
\begin_inset Formula $n=2$
\end_inset

.
 The probability density function is defined by the following equation:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f_{p}(\emph{\boldsymbol{x};\boldsymbol{\mu},\kappa)}=C_{p}(\kappa)\exp(\kappa\boldsymbol{\mu}^{T}\boldsymbol{x})
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
C_{p}(\kappa)=\frac{\kappa^{p/2-1}}{(2\pi)^{p}I_{p/2-1}(\kappa)}
\]

\end_inset

 and intuitively is an approximation for the normal distribution on the
 hypersphere.
\end_layout

